
install postgres from MacOS cli:
	>brew install postgresql

initiate new database cluster at 'data area' folder: 
	>initdb /usr/local/var/postgres
start server: 
 option 1: 
 	>postgres -D /usr/local/var/postgres
 option 2:
 	> pg_ctl -D /usr/local/var/postgres -l logfile start
 
 create new database:
  >createdb mydb
  >start interactive terminal 'psql'
   psql -l
   psql mydb
   mydb(# CREATE TABLE test (name varchar(20), age smallint);
   mydb(# INSERT INTO test VALUES ('Sam', 40);
      
 
 download newest jdbc driver for postgresql
 include this jar-file driver into project's build path
